  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Responsive Image Wrapper Positioning for Image Error States\n\nCorrect the CSS positioning property for `.responsive-image-wrapper.image-error` elements to resolve sizing issues when images fail to load.\n\nRequirements:\n- Update `.responsive-image-wrapper.image-error` CSS rule to use `position: initial` instead of current positioning value\n- Verify that image error state dimensions now render correctly\n- Test that the change doesn't break layout for successful image loads\n- Ensure the fix works across different viewport sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)\n- Check for any parent container layout conflicts that might be affected by this change\n- Validate that other states of `.responsive-image-wrapper` (loading, success) remain unaffected",
  "title": "Fix image error state positioning in responsive wrapper",
